---
title: Creamy Chicken Pot Pie Includes recyclable aluminum tray
description: Who has time to make homemade crust on a weeknight? Not us! Enter: biscuit dough. Layer the dough over a cozy mix of tender precooked chicken, peas, corn, and cream sauce in our convenient oven-ready tray, then bake for a golden-brown topping. The result is a hearty dinner that’s easy as pie to make.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6761a2d5bdfa7f79d1f16a32-9b5807b7.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6761a2d5bdfa7f79d1f16a32-en-US.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 820 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 76 g
  sugar: 22 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1740 mg
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-chicken-pot-pie-6761a2d5bdfa7f79d1f16a32
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven to 375 degrees.

Drain @corn{1%unit}. Place @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #bowl and bring to room temperature.

In a separate small #microwave-safe bowl{}, whisk together @cream sauce base{4%oz} and @cornstarch{1%tbsp}. Microwave until bubbling, ~{45-60%seconds}. Carefully remove from microwave and whisk to combine.

In #oven-ready aluminum tray{}, using your hands, break up @sous vide chopped chicken{8%oz} into pieces. Stir in corn, @peas{4%oz}, cornstarch mixture, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{} until thoroughly combined.

> For 4 servings, divide everything between two trays, using 1⁄2 tsp sugar for each tray.

Remove @buttermilk biscuits{6%oz} from package. Peel apart each biscuit at the center to create two thinner biscuits; slightly flatten each round using your hands. Evenly top filling with biscuit rounds.

Bake, uncovered, on middle rack until biscuits are golden brown and filling is bubbling, ~{30-35%minutes}. Carefully check bottoms of biscuits for doneness.

> For 4 servings, bake two trays side by side on middle rack.

Once pot pie is done, brush biscuits with softened @?butter{}.

Let pot pie cool at least ~{5%minutes}. Divide between bowls and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.